# pyenv
#   For a library or script, you may not want to ignore these files if you want to embed
#   version information in wheel or installer files.
#   For example, when creating a package for distribution, you may want to keep the version
#   of the language to indicate which versions it's compatible with. However, if you are
#   building a library that will be used in multiple versions of Python, you might want
#   to ignore these files.
.python-version

